main event: In October 1957, a witness in Dolinsk, USSR, observed a strange flying object that caused a tremendous sound and made the house shake.
interesting points: The witness described the object making a significant noise, resembling a jet breaking the sound barrier., The object was seen high above in the western skies., The sighting lasted only a brief moment as the object disappeared shortly after being noticed., The event was classified as a ground visual observation., Initial conclusions suggested the object might have been a balloon or aircraft, but it remained unidentified due to insufficient data.
witness description: the witness felt a tremendous sound and shaking of the house
